Product Description

UGREEN Cat7 Cat6 Cat5 RJ45 Network Keystone Jack Line Coupler Female to Female

Ugreen RJ45 Female to Female Network Jack In-Line Coupler extend the length of a Ethernet patch cable.

Constructed of high-impact, fire-retardant plastic and nickel plated contacts, these couplers meet or exceed Category 7 performance in compliance with the TIA/EIA 568-C.2 standard.

Specification

  1. Connectors: RJ45 8P8C, Nickel Plating;
  2. TIA/EIA 568-C.2 Verified;
  3. RoHS compliant.
  4. Network Speed: up to 10 Gbps

Read more

Extend the length of your Ethernet patch cable.

More cost-effective and time-saving than swapping-out short cables for longer ones, UGREEN Ethernet Cable Coupler is remarkably less expensive and snaps into place in seconds to keep data flowing.

High Speed up to 10Gbps.

The RJ45 connector can speed up to 10 gigabite for connecting Cat7/Cat6 ethernet cable.

Stable connection and durable.

UGREEN network coupler build with pure copper plated tentacles which can reduce the connections / disconnections to provide port protection.ABS material shell, flame retardant and durable.

Stable Connection

Compatible with all kinds of networks both home and industrial. Snap with all kinds of RJ45 connections (cat7, cat6, cat5, cat5e).

Pure copper plated tentacles

Pure copper plated tentacles ensure strong signal transmission and high-speed performance.

ABS material

UGREEN RJ45 coupler is made of high quality ABS material, flame retardant and stable.

      Question:
      Will the power in a POE cable transfer through this?
      Answer:
      >> I guess it should work, since power travels through the same wires as data. <<
      Not necessarily. Power wire size requirements are generally much higher than data requirements. For example, my house has electric shades and drapes. They are connected together with a 4 conductor cable. The 2 data wires are 22 gauge, … see more       >> I guess it should work, since power travels through the same wires as data. <<
      Not necessarily. Power wire size requirements are generally much higher than data requirements. For example, my house has electric shades and drapes. They are connected together with a 4 conductor cable.       2.0 out of 5 stars Works well but is not 'keystone' as advertised
      Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 17, 2020
      Verified Purchase
      This product works well. I'm transferring gigabit ethernet speeds through it and it works as advertised. It seems well built. The reason for my 2* review is that it's advertised as 'keystone' mount in the title, which means it will fit in a standard sized keystone plate, which this does not. I specifically purchased this to snap into a keystone wall box, and it's way too big to fit.

      tl;dr:
      Need this for wiring cables? Buy it, it will do the job as advertised. Need this for fitting into a keystone plate as it's advertised as? Steer clear.
